===Achievements ===
Burleson was a state semifinalist in the 4A state title in football in 2001.  In 2006, Burleson won the 4-A District Championship in football over [[Mansfield Summit High School]]. Burleson High School is also where the famous [[See You at the Pole]] tradition began and where the famous [[Kelly Clarkson]] graduated from. 

==Student life==
===Organizations===
The school has over 30 organizations, which include community service, foreign language, sports, and [[University Interscholastic League|UIL]] organizations.

=== Media ===
"Elk TV" first aired in the 2005-2006 school year. It is the school's weekly news program which is written, directed and edited by the students in the broadcast journalism class.

== Feeder patterns ==
The following elementary schools feed into Burleson High School, followed by their mascots:
*Academy at Nola Dunn Elementary,
*Bransom Elementary, Bobcats
*Frasier Elementary, Bears
*Mound Elementary, Mustangs
*Norwood Elementary, Vikings
*Stribling Elementary, Stars
*Taylor Elementary, Texans

The following middle schools feed into Burleson
High School, followed by their mascots:
*Nick Kerr Middle School, Cougars
*Pauline G. Hughes Middle School, Huskies

== Notable alumni ==
*[[Kelly Clarkson]] singer, songwriter, actress, and [[American Idol]] season 1 winner
*[[Stacy Sykora]] is a 2 time Olympian. She competes in volleyball. Once in 2000 and again in 2004 and is a Burleson alumnist.

